‚≠ê STEP 1 ‚Äî Create Your Visio Install XML
Go to:
üëâ https://config.office.com

1. Click Create ‚Üí New Configuration
2. Under Products and releases choose:

Office Suites ‚Üí Microsoft 365 Apps for enterprise
Scroll down to Apps

Select Visio (Plan 2/Volume/etc.)

3. Select Architecture:
64-bit (recommended)

4. Under Language, choose:
English (en-us) or your preferred

5. Under Installation Options:
Turn OFF Office apps you don‚Äôt want
Keep only Visio enabled (optional)

6. Export the configuration file:
Save as:

Visio-install.xml


If you want, I can generate this file for you automatically.

‚≠ê STEP 2 ‚Äî Package the Installer for Intune

You need Office Deployment Tool (ODT).

Download from:
üëâ https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/download/details.aspx?id=49117

Extract contents.

Create a folder:

C:\Visio-Intune\


Copy into it:

setup.exe

Visio-install.xml

Your folder should look like:

C:\Visio-Intune\setup.exe
C:\Visio-Intune\Visio-install.xml

‚≠ê STEP 3 ‚Äî Convert Folder into an Intune .intunewin Package

Download IntuneWinAppUtil:
üëâ https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/mem/intune/apps/intune-win32-apps

In PowerShell or CMD:

IntuneWinAppUtil.exe -c "C:\Visio-Intune" -s "setup.exe" -o "C:\Output"


This creates:

C:\Output\setup.intunewin

‚≠ê STEP 4 ‚Äî Upload to Intune

Go to:
Intune Admin Center ‚Üí Apps ‚Üí Windows apps ‚Üí Add

Choose:

App type: Windows app (Win32)

Upload:

setup.intunewin

Program settings:

Install command:

setup.exe /configure Visio-install.xml


Uninstall command:

setup.exe /configure Visio-uninstall.xml


(If you want, I‚Äôll generate the uninstall XML.)

‚≠ê STEP 5 ‚Äî Detection Rules

Choose:

‚úî Manually configure detection rules

Rule type:

File or Registry

Example registry detection for Visio:
HKLM\SOFTWARE\Microsoft\Office\ClickToRun\Configuration
Value: ProductReleaseIds
Contains: VisioProRetail

or File

Path: C:\Program Files\Microsoft Office\root\Office16
File: VISIO.EXE

‚≠ê STEP 6 ‚Äî Assign to Users / Devices

Assign to:

A user group with Visio licenses
or

Devices (if volume license)

Deployment Mode:

Required (automatic install)
or

Available (user installs from Company Portal)
